# PrefixComponent in std::path - Rust

```
pub struct PrefixComponent<'a> { /* private fields */ }
```

Expand description

A structure wrapping a Windows path prefix as well as its unparsed string representation.

In addition to the parsed [`Prefix`](enum.Prefix.html "enum std::path::Prefix") information returned by [`kind`](about:blank/struct.PrefixComponent.html#method.kind "method std::path::PrefixComponent::kind"), `PrefixComponent` also holds the raw and unparsed [`OsStr`](../ffi/struct.OsStr.html "struct std::ffi::OsStr") slice, returned by [`as_os_str`](about:blank/struct.PrefixComponent.html#method.as_os_str "method std::path::PrefixComponent::as_os_str").

Instances of this `struct` can be obtained by matching against the [`Prefix` variant](about:blank/enum.Component.html#variant.Prefix "variant std::path::Component::Prefix") on [`Component`](enum.Component.html "enum std::path::Component").

Does not occur on Unix.

## [§](#examples)Examples

```
use std::path::{Component, Path, Prefix};
use std::ffi::OsStr;

let path = Path::new(r"c:\you\later\");
match path.components().next().unwrap() {
    Component::Prefix(prefix_component) => {
        assert_eq!(Prefix::Disk(b'C'), prefix_component.kind());
        assert_eq!(OsStr::new("c:"), prefix_component.as_os_str());
    }
    _ => unreachable!(),
}
```
